Anyways, I'll put in my impression of Ghouldan from the limited dealings I had with him.  Just as Edagon said, he seems to be a GREAT guy if you are in his inner circle.  If you are not, go to hell.  When I first moved over to RZ, Ghouldan and friends were kind enough to invite me on a few raids to pick up some rotting loots.  I was even offered a couple of Skyshrine MQs.  However, when Ghouldan learned I was an AD applicant, I was told the MQs had been sold or something and I was no longer asked along on raids EXCEPT when they had no DPS.<br>
<br>
Which brings me to my next point.  I can't remember when it was or who it was, but we (a few AD and a few peeps from some other guild I can't remember the name of) were killing Vindi when some Reverant gave me a tell saying that we should not be helping that guild cause they should not get Vindi loots if they can't handle it themselves.  I shrugged it off.  The next day, I get a tell from Ghouldan AND the very same person who had given me a tell the day before asking if I would help them with the Cursed cause they were low on DPS.  Hypocrisy anyone?<br>
<br>
To sum up my impressions: Ghouldan is the greatest guy in the world ... if you are in his inner circle of friends.  He will work VERY hard and get you loot ... if you are in his inner circle.  His hard work and dertermination reward him with the highest loyalty ... if you are in his inner circle.  If you are not in that inner circle, kindly get the fuck out of my sight.<br>
