<br>
Ghouldan is a very good at playing his class and leading raids, and perhaps one of the best SK pullers on RZ, and his dedication to his guild is unquestionable.<br>
<br>
When it came to dealing with Ghouldan as an officer in a guild 'competing' for the same content, I had more headaches than I care to remember - and we had each other on ignore for a very long time.<br>
<br>
He had huge issues with SoD receiving help from friends, but would have no problem receiving critical help from his own friends - and I think Rehoboam is pretty spot on, Ghouldan is a good guy as long as you are working alongside him.<br>
<br>
I do think the way he acted though was in what he considered 'his guilds' best interest, but all the same it was very very frustrating to be on the end of, because while looking out for the best for his guild, he had no qualms about stepping on everyone who got in his way.<br>
<br>
That said - me and Ghouldan butted heads forvery long time, and I think the fact that we were doing the same mobs Rev was doing with outside help infuriated Ghouldan and as such my assesment is pretty biased, but I tried to be as objective as I could.<br>
